<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - LIFT AXLE SYSTEMS - FIXED (RIGID) AXLE ASSEMBLIES -
        MAINTENANCE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>MAINTENANCE SCHEDULE</title>
            <para>Perform the maintenance procedures listed in the Periodic Maintenance table at the indicated intervals
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="t14019d">TABLE 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <table id="t14019d" tblwidth="full-page">
                <title>Periodic Maintenance on Fixed Lift Axles</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.71*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.10*"/>
                    <colspec colname="COLSPEC2" colwidth="1.41*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ITEM/SYSTEM</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">INTERVAL</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC2" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">PROCEDURE</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Brakes</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Daily before moving/operating</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                                <para>Check for proper brake operation.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Structural Integrity</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Daily before operating</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                                <para>Inspect for signs of structural damage, cracks or wear in all components of
                                    suspension parts (arms, hangers, axle seats, etc.).
                                </para>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">INFORM MANUFACTURER IMMEDIATELY OF ANY STRUCTURAL DAMAGE OF ANY
                                        KIND.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Air Control System</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Daily before operating</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                                <para>Check for air leaks</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Bushings</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Every 30 days</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                                <para>Check for excessive wear or movement</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Axle Mounted Air Tank</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Monthly in dry environment</para>
                                <para>Daily in humid environment</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                                <para>Drain condensation from tank.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Bolts/Fasteners</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Every 6 months.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC2">
                                <para>Retorque bolts to the values indicated in the
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_42.xml" xrefid="hl14019080">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>
                                    section
                                    <xref refid="hl14019080"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>AIR TANK MAINTENANCE</title>
            <para>Drain cocks are installed in the bottom of each reservoir in the air system to provide a convenient
                means of draining condensation. Drain air tank regularly. Local conditions govern frequency. In dry
                climates, for example, once a month may be sufficient, while in humid areas it may be necessary to drain
                reservoirs daily. The drain cock is open when the handle is parallel to the drain cock body and closed
                when the handle is at right angles to the body.
            </para>
            <para>When draining the air reservoirs, open the drain cock and let the air bleed off. Be sure to leave the
                drain cock open until all drainage stops, then close the drain cock.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>TORQUE SETTINGS</title>
            <para>Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s14019_42.xml" xrefid="hl14019080">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>
                section
                <xref refid="hl14019080"/>
                for all torque settings.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
